Mariupol, Ukraine: A model city of 'new Russia'
description: Since 2015, photographer Gabriele Micalizzi has been documenting the Donbas region from the Russian side of the front line, an area where Moscow enforces very strict access conditions for journalists. In November, he secured permission to enter Donetsk Oblast, a region of occupied Ukraine, and traveled to Mariupol, a city destroyed by Russian forces in 2022, which has since been colonized and rebuilt in record time.

description: Emirati-backed separatists in Yemen said they would press ahead with their campaign to restore an independent south after air strikes blamed on Saudi Arabia hit their positions.

headline: In Belarus, the shadow political prisoners
description: Beyond the roughly 1,000 political prisoners who have been officially identified, hundreds more languish in prison without being recorded. The regime of Alexander Lukashenko has done everything it can to keep them hidden and ensure they are forgotten.

headline: At Marseille's MuCEM, an exhibition explores the sunken island of Ferdinandea
description: Until September 20, 2026, at the MuCEM in Marseille, artist Clément Cogitore dedicates an exhibit to Ferdinandea, a short-lived island off the coast of Sicily that appeared in the 19th century following a volcanic eruption and was later submerged.

headline: In the home of Zara, at the heart of fashion photography
description: In just four years, Marta Ortega Pérez, head of the Spanish group Inditex, has transformed her foundation in A Coruña, Galicia, into a venue showcasing the greats of fashion photography. Following retrospectives dedicated to Peter Lindbergh, Irving Penn and Helmut Newton, American photographer Annie Leibovitz has been exhibiting her work in this former industrial building in the port since the end of November.

Why more young people are turning to religion
description: Many researchers have observed a resurgence of religious commitment among young people in France, often accompanied by a certain rigorism. This renewed spiritual quest is linked both to the anxieties of our era and, at times, a search for identity.

headline: Lumpy skin disease: Why are French farms experiencing so many animal disease outbreaks?
description: Combined with globalized trade, the overall rise in temperatures driven by human-induced climate change has allowed insects and other vectors of diseases once confined to tropical regions to spread northward.

headline: Algeria demands 'apologies' and 'reparations' from France for its colonial past
description: Algerian MPs passed a law on Wednesday, December 24, to 'criminalize French colonization,' amid ongoing diplomatic tensions between Algiers and Paris.
